    "title": "Principal Instructional Designer at Khan Academy India",
    "description": "Khan Academy India invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Instructional Designer at our Indore location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Khan Academy India:\nKhan Academy India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor student progress and provide timely feedback\n• Conduct parent-teacher meetings and update parents on student performance\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Develop and deliver engaging lesson plans for students\n• Contribute to school newsletter, blogs, and other publications\n• Participate in school events, workshops, and training programs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Content Creation\n• Proficiency in Educational Technology\n• Proficiency in Data Analysis\n• Proficiency in IB Curriculum\n• Proficiency in Mentoring\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n• Proficiency in Curriculum Development\n• Proficiency in Lesson Planning\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Referral bonus program\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Indore, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Khan Academy India!",
